307 !> Reads the namcouple
308 
309 SUBROUTINE oasis_namcouple_init()
310 
311  IMPLICIT NONE
312 
313  !-----------------------------------------------------------
314  INTEGER(kind=ip_i4_p) :: n, nv, n1, n2, loc
315  INTEGER(kind=ip_i4_p) :: ja, jf, jc
316  INTEGER(kind=ip_i4_p) :: il_iost
317  INTEGER(kind=ip_i4_p) :: maxunit
318  CHARACTER(len=*),parameter :: subname='(oasis_namcouple_init)'
319  !-----------------------------------------------------------
320 
321  CALL oasis_unitget(nulin)
322  OPEN (nulin,file =cl_namcouple,status='OLD', form ='FORMATTED', iostat = il_iost)
323 
324  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
325  IF (il_iost .NE. 0) THEN
326  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) ' ERROR opening namcouple file ',trim(cl_namcouple),' with unit number ',nulin
327  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
328  ELSE
329  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,' open namcouple file ',trim(cl_namcouple),' with unit number ',nulin
330  ENDIF
331  ENDIF
332 
333  CALL inipar_alloc()
334  CALL alloc()
335  CALL inipar()
336  !
337  ! Close namcouple unit
338  close(nulin)
339 
340  CALL oasis_unitfree(nulin)
341 
342  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
343  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,' allocating ig_final_nfield',ig_final_nfield
344  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
345  ENDIF
346 
347  allocate(namsrcfld(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
348  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namsrcfld" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
349 
350  allocate(namdstfld(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
351  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namdstfld" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
352 
353  allocate(namsrcgrd(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
354  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namsrcgrd" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
355 
356  allocate(namsrc_nx(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
357  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namsrc_nx" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
358 
359  allocate(namsrc_ny(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
360  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namsrc_ny" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
361 
362  allocate(namdstgrd(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
363  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namdstgrd" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
364 
365  allocate(namdst_nx(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
366  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namdst_nx" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
367 
368  allocate(namdst_ny(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
369  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namdst_ny" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
370 
371  allocate(namfldseq(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
372  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namfldseq" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
373 
374  allocate(namfldops(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)
375  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error in "namfldops" allocation of experiment module',il_err,1)
376 
377  allocate(namfldtrn(ig_final_nfield), stat=il_err)

454 
455  namsrcfld(:) = trim(cspval)
456  namdstfld(:) = trim(cspval)
457  namsrcgrd(:) = trim(cspval)
458  namsrc_nx(:) = 0
459  namsrc_ny(:) = 0
460  namdstgrd(:) = trim(cspval)
461  namdst_nx(:) = 0
462  namdst_ny(:) = 0
463  namfldseq(:) = -1
464  namfldops(:) = -1
465  namfldtrn(:) = ip_instant
466  namfldcon(:) = ip_cnone
467  namfldcoo(:) = "bfb"
468  namflddti(:) = -1
469  namfldlag(:) = 0
470  nammapfil(:) = "idmap"
471  nammaploc(:) = "src"
472  nammapopt(:) = "bfb"
473  namrstfil(:) = trim(cspval)
474  naminpfil(:) = trim(cspval)
475  namchecki(:) = .false.
476  namchecko(:) = .false.
477  namfldsmu(:) = 1.0_ip_realwp_p
478  namfldsad(:) = 0.0_ip_realwp_p
479  namflddmu(:) = 1.0_ip_realwp_p
480  namflddad(:) = 0.0_ip_realwp_p
481 
482  namscrmet(:) = trim(cspval)
483  namscrnor(:) = trim(cspval)
484  namscrtyp(:) = trim(cspval)
485  namscrord(:) = trim(cspval)
486  namscrres(:) = trim(cspval)
487  namscrvam(:) = 1.0_ip_realwp_p
488  namscrnbr(:) = -1
489  namscrbin(:) = -1
490 
491 ! maxunit = max(maxval(iga_unitmod),1024)
492 ! maxunit = 1024
493 ! IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
494 ! WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,' maximum unit number = ',maxunit
495 ! CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)

505  namnorest = nnorest

507  nammatxrd = nmatxrd
508  namwgtopt = nwgtopt

510  namsrcfld(jf) = cg_input_field(jf)
511  namdstfld(jf) = cg_output_field(jf)
512  namfldseq(jf) = ig_total_nseqn(jf)
513  namfldops(jf) = ig_total_state(jf)
514  IF (namfldops(jf) == ip_auxilary) THEN
515  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) jf,' ERROR: AUXILARY NOT SUPPORTED'
516  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
517  ENDIF
518  IF (namfldops(jf) == ip_ignored) THEN
519  namfldops(jf) = ip_exported
520  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
521  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,jf,'WARNING: IGNORED converted to EXPORTED'
522  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
523  ENDIF
524  ENDIF

526  namfldops(jf) = ip_expout

529  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
530  ENDIF
531  ENDIF

539  namsrc_nx(jf) = nlonbf(ig_number_field(jf))
540  namsrc_ny(jf) = nlatbf(ig_number_field(jf))
541  namdstgrd(jf) = trim(cficaf(ig_number_field(jf)))
542  namdst_nx(jf) = nlonaf(ig_number_field(jf))
543  namdst_ny(jf) = nlataf(ig_number_field(jf))
544  DO ja = 1, ig_ntrans(ig_number_field(jf))
545 
546  IF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'SCRIPR') THEN
547  namscrmet(jf) = trim(cmap_method(ig_number_field(jf)))
548  namscrnor(jf) = trim(cnorm_opt(ig_number_field(jf)))
549  namscrtyp(jf) = trim(cfldtype(ig_number_field(jf)))
550  namscrord(jf) = trim(corder(ig_number_field(jf)))
551  namscrres(jf) = trim(crsttype(ig_number_field(jf)))
552  namscrvam(jf) = varmul(ig_number_field(jf))
553  namscrnbr(jf) = nscripvoi(ig_number_field(jf))
554  namscrbin(jf) = nbins(ig_number_field(jf))
555  IF (trim(namscrtyp(jf)) /= 'SCALAR') THEN
556  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) subname,jf,'WARNING: SCRIPR weights generation &
557  & supported only for SCALAR mapping, not '//trim(namscrtyp(jf))
558  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
559  ENDIF
560 
561  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'MAPPING') THEN
562  nammapfil(jf) = trim(cmap_file(ig_number_field(jf)))
563  nammaploc(jf) = trim(cmaptyp(ig_number_field(jf)))
564  nammapopt(jf) = trim(cmapopt(ig_number_field(jf)))
565 
566  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'CONSERV') THEN
567  namfldcon(jf) = ip_cnone
568  namfldcoo(jf) = trim(cconopt(ig_number_field(jf)))
569  IF (cconmet(ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'GLOBAL') namfldcon(jf) = ip_cglobal
570  IF (cconmet(ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'GLBPOS') namfldcon(jf) = ip_cglbpos
571  IF (cconmet(ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BASBAL') namfldcon(jf) = ip_cbasbal
572  IF (cconmet(ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BASPOS') namfldcon(jf) = ip_cbaspos
573  IF (namfldcon(jf) .EQ. ip_cnone) THEN
574  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) subname,jf,'WARNING: CONSERV option not supported: '//&
575  &trim(cconmet(ig_number_field(jf)))
576  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
577  ENDIF
578 
579  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'CHECKIN' ) THEN
580  namchecki(jf) = .true.
581 
582  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'CHECKOUT') THEN
583  namchecko(jf) = .true.
584 
585  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BLASOLD') THEN
586  namfldsmu(jf) = afldcobo(ig_number_field(jf))
587  DO jc = 1, nbofld(ig_number_field(jf))
588  IF (trim(cbofld(jc,ig_number_field(jf))) == 'CONSTANT') THEN
589  namfldsad(jf) = abocoef(jc,ig_number_field(jf))
590  ELSE
591  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) subname,jf,'ERROR: BLASOLD only supports CONSTANT: '//&
592  &trim(cbofld(jc,ig_number_field(jf)))
593  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
594  ENDIF
595  ENDDO
596 
597  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BLASNEW') THEN
598  namflddmu(jf) = afldcobn(ig_number_field(jf))
599  DO jc = 1, nbnfld(ig_number_field(jf))
600  IF (trim(cbnfld(jc,ig_number_field(jf))) == 'CONSTANT') THEN
601  namflddad(jf) = abncoef(jc,ig_number_field(jf))
602  ELSE
603  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) subname,jf,'ERROR: BLASNEW only supports CONSTANTS: '//&
604  &trim(cbofld(jc,ig_number_field(jf)))
605  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
606  ENDIF
607  ENDDO
608 
609  ENDIF ! canal
610  ENDDO ! ig_ntrans
611  ENDIF ! ig_number_field
612  ENDDO ! ig_final_nfield
613 
614  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
615  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
616  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,'namlogprt,t ',namlogprt, namtlogprt
617  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,'namuntmin,max ',namuntmin, namuntmax
618  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,'namnorest ',namnorest
619  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,'nammapdec ',trim(nammapdec)
620  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,'nammatxrd ',trim(nammatxrd)
621  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,'namwgtopt ',trim(namwgtopt)
622  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
623  DO n = 1,nnamcpl
624  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namsrcfld ',trim(namsrcfld(n))
625  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namdstfld ',trim(namdstfld(n))
626  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namsrcgrd ',trim(namsrcgrd(n))
627  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namsrc_nx ',namsrc_nx(n)
628  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namsrc_ny ',namsrc_ny(n)
629  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namdstgrd ',trim(namdstgrd(n))
630  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namdst_nx ',namdst_nx(n)
631  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namdst_ny ',namdst_ny(n)
632  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namfldseq ',namfldseq(n)
633  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namfldops ',namfldops(n)
634  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namfldtrn ',namfldtrn(n)
635  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namfldcon ',namfldcon(n)
636  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namfldcoo ',trim(namfldcoo(n))
637  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namflddti ',namflddti(n)
638  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namfldlag ',namfldlag(n)
639  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'nammapfil ',trim(nammapfil(n))
640  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'nammaploc ',trim(nammaploc(n))
641  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'nammapopt ',trim(nammapopt(n))
642  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namrstfil ',trim(namrstfil(n))
643  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'naminpfil ',trim(naminpfil(n))
644  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namchecki ',namchecki(n)
645  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namchecko ',namchecko(n)
646  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namfldsmu ',namfldsmu(n)
647  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'nbofld ',nbofld(n)
648  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namfldsad ',namfldsad(n)
649  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namflddmu ',namflddmu(n)
650  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'nbnfld ',nbnfld(n)
651  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namflddad ',namflddad(n)
652  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namscrmet ',trim(namscrmet(n))
653  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namscrnor ',trim(namscrnor(n))
654  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namscrtyp ',trim(namscrtyp(n))
655  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namscrord ',trim(namscrord(n))
656  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namscrres ',trim(namscrres(n))
657  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namscrvam ',namscrvam(n)
658  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namscrnbr ',namscrnbr(n)
659  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,n,'namscrbin ',namscrbin(n)
660  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
661  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
662  ENDDO
663  ENDIF
664 
665  !--- compute seq sort ---
666  namsort2nn(:) = -1
667  DO nv = 1,nnamcpl
668  loc = nv ! default at end
669  n1 = 1
670  DO WHILE (loc == nv .and. n1 < nv)
671  IF (namfldseq(nv) < namfldseq(namsort2nn(n1))) loc = n1
672  n1 = n1 + 1
673  ENDDO
674  ! nv goes into loc location, shift THEN set
675  DO n1 = nv,loc+1,-1
676  namsort2nn(n1) = namsort2nn(n1-1)
677  ENDDO
678  namsort2nn(loc) = nv
679  ENDDO
680 
681  DO nv = 1,nnamcpl
682  namnn2sort(namsort2nn(nv)) = nv
683  ENDDO
684 
685  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
686  DO nv = 1,nnamcpl
687  n1 = namsort2nn(nv)
688  n2 = namnn2sort(nv)
689  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,' sort ',nv,n1,n2,namfldseq(n1)
690  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
691  ENDDO
692  ENDIF
693 
694  !--- check they are sorted ---
695  DO n = 2,nnamcpl
696  IF (namfldseq(namsort2nn(n)) < namfldseq(namsort2nn(n-1))) THEN
697  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,' ERROR in seq sort')
698  ENDIF
699  ENDDO
700 
701  CALL dealloc()
702 
703  ! CALL oasis_debug_exit(subname)
704 
705 END SUBROUTINE oasis_namcouple_init

707 !===============================================================================
708 
709 !> Reads the namcouple to allocate arrays
710 
711 SUBROUTINE inipar_alloc()
712 
713 !****
714 ! *****************************
715 ! * OASIS ROUTINE - LEVEL 0 *
716 ! * ------------- ------- *
717 ! *****************************
718 
719 !**** *inipar_alloc* - Get main run parameters to allocate arrays
720 
721 ! Purpose:
722 ! -------
723 ! Reads out run parameters.
724 
725 !** Interface:
726 ! ---------
727 ! *CALL* *inipar_alloc*
728 
729 ! Input:
730 ! -----
731 ! None
732 
733 ! Output:
734 ! ------
735 ! None
736 !
737 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
738 
739  IMPLICIT NONE
740 
741  !* ---------------------------- Local declarations --------------------
742 
743  CHARACTER*5000 clline, clline_aux, clvari
744  CHARACTER*3 clind
745  CHARACTER*2 cldeb
746  CHARACTER*1 clequa
747  CHARACTER*8 clwork
748  CHARACTER*8 clstrg
749  CHARACTER*7 cl_bsend
750 
751  CHARACTER(len=32), DIMENSION(:), ALLOCATABLE :: cl_aux
752  CHARACTER(len=32) :: keyword
753  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p) il_varid, il_len, il_err, il_maxanal
754  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p) nlonbf_notnc, nlatbf_notnc, &
755  nlonaf_notnc, nlataf_notnc
756  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p) iind, il_redu, ib, il_aux, il_auxbf, &
757  il_auxaf, istatus, il_id
758  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p) :: ja,jz,jm,jf,ILEN,n,ios
759  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p) :: ig_clim_maxport
760  LOGICAL :: lg_bsend,endflag
761  LOGICAL :: found, readfile
762  CHARACTER(len=*),parameter :: subname='(mod_oasis_namcouple:inipar_alloc)'
763 
764  !* ---------------------------- Poema verses --------------------------
765 
766  ! CALL oasis_debug_enter(subname)
767 
768  ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
769 
770  !* 1. Get basic info for the simulation
771  ! ---------------------------------
772 
773  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
774  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
775  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname
776  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' ROUTINE inipar_alloc - Level 0'
777  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' ******************** *******'
778  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
779  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' Initialization of run parameters'
780  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
781  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' Reading input file namcouple'
782  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
783  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
784  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
785  ENDIF
786 
787  !* Initialization
788  ig_direct_nfield = 0
789  ig_nfield = 0
790  lg_oasis_field = .true.
791 
792  !* Check for typos in keywords, read all lines until file is at end
793 
794  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
795  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' Executing valid keyword check '
796  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
797  ENDIF
798  readfile = .true.
799  DO WHILE (readfile)
800  READ(nulin, fmt=rform, end=501) clline
801  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
802  IF (ios == 0) THEN
803  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
804  IF (clvari(1:1) == "$") THEN
805  found = .false.
806  DO n = 1, nkeywords
807  IF (clvari == keyword_list(n)) found = .true.
808  ENDDO
809  IF (.NOT. found) THEN
810  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
811  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' Found invalid keyword = '//trim(clvari)
812  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
813  ENDIF
814  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,' ERROR: invalid keyword = '//trim(clvari))
815  ELSE
816  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
817  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' Found valid keyword = '//trim(clvari)
818  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
819  ENDIF
820  ENDIF
821  ENDIF
822  ELSE
823  GOTO 501
824  ENDIF
825  ENDDO
826 501 CONTINUE
827 
828  if (mpi_rank_global == 0) WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
829 
830  !* Get number of models involved in this simulation
831 
832  keyword = clmod

1305  il_maxanal = maxval(ig_ntrans)
1306 
1307  !* Alloc array of restart file names
1308 
1309  ALLOCATE (cficinp(ig_nfield), stat=il_err)
1310  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error: cficinp allocation of '//trim(subname),il_err,1)
1311  cficinp(:)=' '
1312  DO ib = 1, ig_final_nfield
1313  IF (lg_state(ib)) cficinp(ig_number_field(ib))=cg_restart_file(ib)
1314  ENDDO
1315 #ifdef use_netCDF
1316  !tcx?
1317  ! istatus=NF_OPEN(cg_restart_file(1), NF_NOWRITE, il_id)
1318  ! IF (istatus .eq. NF_NOERR) THEN
1319  ! lncdfrst = .true.
1320  ! ELSE
1321 #endif
1322  lncdfrst = .false.
1323 #ifdef use_netCDF
1324  ! ENDIF
1325  ! istatus=NF_CLOSE(il_id)
1326 #endif
1327  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1328  WRITE(nulprt1, *) 'lncdfrst =', lncdfrst
1329  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1330  ENDIF
1331 
1332  !* Alloc array needed to get analysis names
1333 
1334  ALLOCATE (canal(il_maxanal,ig_nfield),stat=il_err)
1335  IF (il_err.NE.0) CALL prtout('Error: canal allocation of '//trim(subname),il_err,1)
1336  canal(:,:)=' '
1337  ENDIF
1338 
1339  !* Get analysis parameters
1340 
1341  keyword = clstring
1342  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1343  IF (.not.found) THEN
1344  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) trim(keyword)//' not found'
1345  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
1346  ENDIF
1347 
1348  !* Loop on total number of fields (NoF)
1349 
1350  DO jf=1,ig_final_nfield
1351 
1352  !* Initialization
1353 
1354  nlonbf_notnc = 0
1355  nlatbf_notnc = 0
1356  nlonaf_notnc = 0
1357  nlataf_notnc = 0
1358 
1359  !* Skip first line read before
1360 
1361  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1362  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1363 
1364  !* Second line
1365 
1366  !* In the indirect case, reading of second, third, fourth line and analyses
1367  !* lines
1368 
1369  IF (ig_total_state(jf) .NE. ip_input) THEN
1370  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1371  !* First determine what information is on the line
1372  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1373  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 3, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1374  IF (ilen .LT. 0) THEN
1375  !* IF only two words on the line, THEN they are the locator
1376  !* prefixes and the grids file must be in NetCDF format
1377  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1378  IF (lg_state(jf)) cficbf(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
1379  cga_locatorbf(jf) = clvari(1:4)
1380  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1381  IF (lg_state(jf)) cficaf(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
1382  cga_locatoraf(jf) = clvari(1:4)
1383  lncdfgrd = .true.
1384  ELSE
1385  READ(clvari, fmt=2010) clind, clequa, iind
1386  IF (clind .EQ. 'SEQ' .OR. clind .EQ. 'LAG' .AND. clequa .EQ. '=') THEN
1387  !* If 3rd word is an index, THEN first two words are
1388  !* locator prefixes and grids file must be NetCDF format
1389  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1390  IF (lg_state(jf)) cficbf(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
1391  cga_locatorbf(jf) = clvari(1:4)
1392  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1393  IF (lg_state(jf)) cficaf(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
1394  cga_locatoraf(jf) = clvari(1:4)
1395  lncdfgrd = .true.
1396  ELSE
1397  !* If not, the first 4 words are grid dimensions and next
1398  !* 2 words are locator prefixes, and grids file may be or
1399  !* not in NetCDF format
1400  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1401  !* Get number of longitudes for initial field
1402  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1403  WRITE(nulprt1,*)'CLVARI=',trim(clvari)
1404  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1405  ENDIF
1406  READ(clvari, fmt=2004) nlonbf_notnc
1407  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1408  !* Get number of latitudes for initial field
1409  READ(clvari, fmt=2004) nlatbf_notnc
1410  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 3, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1411  !* Get number of longitudes for final field
1412  READ(clvari, fmt=2004) nlonaf_notnc
1413  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 4, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1414  !* Get number of latitudes for final field
1415  READ(clvari, fmt=2004) nlataf_notnc
1416  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 5, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1417  !* Get root name grid-related files (initial field)
1418  IF (lg_state(jf)) cficbf(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
1419  cga_locatorbf(jf) = clvari(1:4)
1420  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 6, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1421  !* Get root name for grid-related files (final field)
1422  IF (lg_state(jf)) cficaf(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
1423  cga_locatoraf(jf) = clvari(1:4)
1424  nlonbf(ig_number_field(jf)) = nlonbf_notnc
1425  nlatbf(ig_number_field(jf)) = nlatbf_notnc
1426  nlonaf(ig_number_field(jf)) = nlonaf_notnc
1427  nlataf(ig_number_field(jf)) = nlataf_notnc
1428 
1429  ENDIF
1430  ENDIF
1431 
1432  !* Read the P 2 P 0 line for exported, expout or auxilary
1433 
1434  IF (lg_state(jf)) THEN
1435  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1436  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1437  ENDIF
1438 
1439  !* Read next line of strings
1440  ! --->>> Stuff related to field transformation
1441 
1442  IF (ig_total_ntrans(jf) .GT. 0) THEN
1443  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1444  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1445  DO ja = 1, ig_total_ntrans(jf)
1446  CALL parse(clline, clvari, ja, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1447  !* Get the whole set of analysis to be performed
1448  IF (lg_state(jf)) canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
1449  ENDDO
1450 
1451  DO ja = 1, ig_total_ntrans(jf)
1452  IF (lg_state(jf)) THEN
1453  cg_c=canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf))
1454  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1455  WRITE(nulprt1,*)'LG_STATE cg_c=', trim(clline)
1456  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1457  ENDIF
1458  IF (cg_c .EQ. 'NOINTERP' .OR. cg_c .EQ. 'REDGLO' .OR. cg_c .EQ. 'INVERT' .OR. &
1459  cg_c .EQ. 'MASK' .OR. cg_c .EQ. 'EXTRAP' .OR. cg_c .EQ. 'CORRECT' .OR. &
1460  cg_c .EQ. 'REDGLO' .OR. cg_c .EQ. 'INTERP' .OR. cg_c .EQ. 'MOZAIC' .OR. &
1461  cg_c .EQ. 'FILLING' .OR. cg_c .EQ. 'MASKP' .OR. cg_c .EQ. 'REVERSE' .OR. &
1462  cg_c .EQ. 'GLORED') THEN
1463  WRITE(tmpstr1,*)' OBSOLETE OPERATION= ',trim(cg_c),' specified in namcouple'
1464  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
1465  ENDIF
1466  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1467  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1468  IF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'SCRIPR')THEN
1469  !* Get field type (scalar/vector)
1470  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 3, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1471  READ(clvari, fmt=2009) clstrg
1472  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BLASOLD') THEN
1473  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1474  !* Get number of additional fields in linear formula
1475  READ(clvari, fmt=2003) nbofld(ig_number_field(jf))
1476  DO ib = 1,nbofld(ig_number_field(jf))
1477  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1478  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1479  ENDDO
1480  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BLASNEW') THEN
1481  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1482  !* Get number of additional fields in linear formula
1483  READ(clvari, fmt=2003) nbnfld(ig_number_field(jf))
1484  DO ib = 1,nbnfld(ig_number_field(jf))
1485  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1486  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1487  ENDDO
1488  ENDIF
1489  ELSE
1490  ! For IGNORED, IGNOUT and OUTPUT, only one line for LOCTRANS
1491  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1492  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1493  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1494  WRITE(nulprt1,*)'OUTPUT clline=', trim(clline)
1495  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1496  ENDIF
1497  ENDIF
1498  ENDDO ! DO ja
1499  ENDIF ! IF (ig_total_ntrans(jf) .GT. 0) THEN
1500  ENDIF !IF (ig_total_state(jf) .NE. ip_input) THEN
1501  ENDDO ! DO jf
1502 
1503  IF (lg_oasis_field) THEN
1504 
1505  !* Search maximum number of fields to be combined in the BLASxxx analyses
1506 
1507  ig_maxcomb = maxval(nbofld)
1508  IF (maxval(nbnfld).GT.ig_maxcomb) ig_maxcomb = maxval(nbnfld)
1509 
1510  !* Search maximum number of neighbors for GAUSSIAN interpolation
1511 
1512  ig_maxnoa = maxval(naisgvoi)
1513  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1514  WRITE(nulprt1,*) 'Max number of neighbors for GAUSSIAN interp : ',ig_maxnoa
1515  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
1516  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1517  ENDIF
1518 
1519  !* Search maximum number of different GAUSSIAN interpolations
1520 
1521  ig_maxnfg = maxval(naisgfl)
1522  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1523  WRITE(nulprt1,*) 'Maximum number of different GAUSSIAN interpolations : ',ig_maxnfg
1524  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
1525  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1526  ENDIF
1527 
1528  ENDIF
1529 
1530  !* Formats
1531 
1532 2001 FORMAT(a9)
1533 2003 FORMAT(i4)
1534 2004 FORMAT(i8)
1535 2009 FORMAT(a8)
1536 2010 FORMAT(a3,a1,i2)
1537 
1538  !* 3. End of routine
1539  ! --------------
1540 
1541  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1542  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
1543  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,'-- End of ROUTINE --'
1544  CALL oasis_flush (nulprt1)
1545  ENDIF
1546 
1547 ! CALL oasis_debug_exit(subname)
1548  RETURN
1549 
1550 END SUBROUTINE inipar_alloc

1556 SUBROUTINE inipar
1557 
1558 !****
1559 ! *****************************
1560 ! * OASIS ROUTINE - LEVEL 0 *
1561 ! * ------------- ------- *
1562 ! *****************************
1563 
1564 !**** *inipar* - Get run parameters
1565 
1566 ! Purpose:
1567 ! -------
1568 ! Reads and prints out run parameters.
1569 
1570 !** Interface:
1571 ! ---------
1572 ! *CALL* *inipar*
1573 
1574 ! Input:
1575 ! -----
1576 ! None
1577 
1578 ! Output:
1579 ! ------
1580 ! None
1581 !
1582 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

1584  IMPLICIT NONE
1585 
1586 !* ---------------------------- Local declarations --------------------
1587 
1588  CHARACTER*5000 clline, clvari
1589  CHARACTER*9 clword

1593  CHARACTER*64 cl_cfname,cl_cfunit

1610 !* ---------------------------- Poema verses --------------------------
1611 
1612 ! CALL oasis_debug_enter(subname)
1613 
1614 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
1615 
1616 !* 1. Get basic info for the simulation
1617 ! ---------------------------------
1618 
1619  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1620  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
1621  WRITE(nulprt1,*) trim(subname)

1623  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' ************** *******'

1625  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' Initialization of run parameters'
1626  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' Reading input file namcouple'
1627  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
1628  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1629  ENDIF
1630 
1631 !* Initialize CHARACTER keywords to locate appropriate input
1632 
1633  !* Initialize some variables
1634  ntime = 0 ; niter = 5
1635  nstep = 86400 ; nitfn=4
1636 
1637  !* First get experiment name
1638 
1639  keyword = cljob
1640  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1641  IF (found .and. mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1642  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** '//trim(keyword)//' is obsolete in OASIS3-MCT'
1643  ENDIF
1644 
1645  !* Get number of models involved in this simulation
1646 
1647  keyword = clmod
1648  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1649  IF (found .and. mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1650  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** '//trim(keyword)//' is obsolete in OASIS3-MCT'
1651  ENDIF
1652 
1653  !* Get hardware info for this OASIS simulation
1654 
1655  keyword = clchan
1656  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1657  IF (found .and. mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1658  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** '//trim(keyword)//' is obsolete in OASIS3-MCT'

1662 
1663  keyword = cltime
1664  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)

1666  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1667  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1668  CALL parse (clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1669  IF (ilen > 0) THEN
1670  READ(clvari, fmt=1004) ntime
1671  ELSE
1672  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) ' ERROR with value associated with '//trim(keyword)
1673  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
1674  ENDIF
1675  ELSE
1676  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) trim(keyword)//' not found in namcouple'
1677  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
1678  ENDIF
1679 
1680  !* Print out total time
1681 
1682  CALL prtout('The total time for this run is ntime =', ntime, 1)
1683 
1684  !* Get initial date for this simulation
1685 
1686  keyword = cldate
1687  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1688  IF (found .and. mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1689  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** '//trim(keyword)//' is obsolete in OASIS3-MCT'
1690  ENDIF
1691 
1692  !* Get number of sequential models involved in this simulation
1693 
1694  keyword = clseq
1695  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1696  IF (found .and. mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1697  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** '//trim(keyword)//' is obsolete in OASIS3-MCT'
1698  ENDIF
1699 
1700  !* Get the information mode for this simulation
1701 
1702  keyword = clhead
1703  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1704  IF (found .and. mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1705  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** '//trim(keyword)//' is obsolete in OASIS3-MCT'
1706  ENDIF

1709 
1710  nlogprt = 2
1711  ntlogprt=0
1712  keyword = clprint
1713  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1714  IF (found) THEN

1716  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1717  CALL parse (clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1718

1720  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1721  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** Nothing on input for '//trim(keyword)
1722  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' Default value 2 will be used '
1723  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
1724  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1725  ENDIF
1726  ELSE
1727  READ(clvari, fmt=1004) nlogprt
1728  CALL parse (clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1729  IF (ilen > 0) THEN
1730  READ(clvari, fmt=1004) ntlogprt
1731  ELSE
1732  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1733  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** Nothing on input for time statistic for '//trim(keyword)
1734  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' Default value 0 will be used '
1735  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
1736  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1737  ENDIF
1738  ENDIF
1739  ENDIF
1740  ENDIF ! found
1741 
1742  !* Print out the printing level
1743 
1744  CALL prtout('The printing level is nlogprt =', nlogprt, 1)
1745  CALL prtout('The time statistics level is ntlogprt =', ntlogprt, 1)
1746 
1747  !* Get the calendar type for this simulation
1748 
1749  keyword = clcal
1750  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1751  IF (found .and. mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1752  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** '//trim(keyword)//' is obsolete in OASIS3-MCT'
1753  ENDIF
1754 
1755  !* Get the allow no restart flag value
1756 
1757  nnorest = .false.
1758  keyword = clrest
1759  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1760  IF (found) THEN
1761  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1762  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1763  CALL parse (clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1764  IF (ilen .LE. 0) THEN
1765  nnorest = .false.
1766  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1767  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** Nothing on input for '//trim(keyword)
1768  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' Default value false will be used '
1769  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
1770  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1771  ENDIF
1772  ELSE
1773  IF (clvari(1:1) == 't' .or. clvari(1:1) == 'T' .or. &
1774  clvari(1:2) == '.t' .or. clvari(1:2) == '.T') then
1775  nnorest = .true.
1776  ENDIF
1777  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1778  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' read '//trim(clvari)//' for '//trim(keyword)
1779  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' set value to ',nnorest
1780  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
1781  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1782  ENDIF
1783  ENDIF
1784  ENDIF ! found
1785 
1786  !* Print out the allow no restart flag
1787 
1788  if (nnorest) then
1789  CALL prtout('The allow_no_restart flag is set to true ',1,1)
1790  else
1791  CALL prtout('The allow_no_restart flag is set to false ',0,1)
1792  endif
1793 
1794  rewind nulin
1795 
1796  !* Get the unit map decomp value
1797 
1798  nmapdec = nmapdec_default
1799  keyword = clmapdec
1800  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)
1801  IF (found) THEN
1802  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
1803  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty, ios=ios)
1804  CALL parse (clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
1805  IF (ilen .LE. 0) THEN
1806  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1807  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' ***WARNING*** Nothing on input for '//trim(keyword)
1808  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' Default value wght will be used '
1809  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
1810  CALL oasis_flush(nulprt1)
1811  ENDIF
1812  ELSE
1813  IF (trim(clvari) == 'decomp_1d' .or. &
1814  trim(clvari) == 'decomp_wghtfile') THEN
1815  nmapdec = clvari
1816  ELSE
1817  CALL prtout('ERROR in namcouple '//trim(keyword)//' argument',jf,1)
1818  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) 'ERROR in namcouple '//trim(keyword)//' argument '//trim(clvari)
1819  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
1820  ENDIF
1821  ENDIF
1822  ENDIF ! found
1823 
1824  !* Print out the mapdec value
1825 
1826  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
1827  write(nulprt1,*) ' The mapdec value is nmapdec = ',trim(nmapdec)
1828  endif
1829 
1830  !* Get the unit matrix read value
1831 
1832  nmatxrd = nmatxrd_default
1833  keyword = clmatxrd
1834  CALL findkeyword (keyword, clline, found)

2325  crsttype(ig_number_field(jf)) .NE. 'REDUCED') THEN
2326  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
2327  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
2328  ENDIF
2329  CALL prtout('ERROR in namcouple for restriction of field',jf,1)
2330  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) '==> must be LATITUDE or LATLON'
2331  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
2332  ENDIF
2333 !*
2334 !* Get number of search bins for SCRIP search
2335  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 5, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2336  READ(clvari, fmt=2003) nbins(ig_number_field(jf))
2337 !* Get normalize option for CONSERV
2338  IF (cmap_method(ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'CONSERV') THEN
2339  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 6, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2340  READ(clvari, fmt=2009)cnorm_opt(ig_number_field(jf))
2341  IF (cnorm_opt(ig_number_field(jf)) .NE. 'FRACAREA' .AND. &
2342  cnorm_opt(ig_number_field(jf)) .NE. 'DESTAREA' .AND. &
2343  cnorm_opt(ig_number_field(jf)) .NE. 'FRACNNEI') THEN
2344  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
2345  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
2346  ENDIF
2347  CALL prtout('ERROR in namcouple for normalize option of field',jf,1)
2348  WRITE(tmpstr1, *) '==> must be FRACAREA, DESTAREA, or FRACNNEI'
2349  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
2350  ENDIF
2351 !* Get order of remapping for CONSERV
2352  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 7, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2353  IF (ilen .LE. 0) THEN
2354  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
2355  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
2356  ENDIF
2357  CALL prtout('ERROR in namcouple for CONSERV for field',jf,1)
2358  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) '==> FIRST must be indicated at end of line'
2359  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
2360  ENDIF
2361  READ(clvari, fmt=2009) corder(ig_number_field(jf))
2362  ELSE
2363  cnorm_opt(ig_number_field(jf))='NONORM'
2364  ENDIF
2365 !* Get number of neighbours for DISTWGT and GAUSWGT
2366  IF (cmap_method(ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'DISTWGT' .or. &
2367  cmap_method(ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'GAUSWGT') THEN
2368  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 6, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2369  IF (ilen .LE. 0) THEN
2370  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
2371  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
2372  ENDIF
2373  CALL prtout('ERROR in namcouple for field',jf,1)
2374  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) '==> Number of neighbours must be indicated on the line'
2375  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
2376  ELSE
2377  READ(clvari, fmt=2003)nscripvoi(ig_number_field(jf))
2378  ENDIF
2379  ENDIF
2380 !* Get gaussian variance for GAUSWGT
2381  IF (cmap_method(ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'GAUSWGT') THEN
2382  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 7, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2383  IF (ilen .LE. 0) THEN
2384  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
2385  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
2386  ENDIF
2387  CALL prtout('ERROR in namcouple for GAUSWGT for field',jf,1)
2388  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) '==> Variance must be indicated at end of line'
2389  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
2390  ELSE
2391  ! Read a string
2392  READ(clvari, fmt=2012) cvarmul
2393  ! and convert it accordingly
2394  IF ( index(cvarmul,'.') == 0 ) then
2395  READ(cvarmul,fmt=2013) ivarmul
2396  varmul(ig_number_field(jf)) = REAL(ivarmul)
2397  ELSE
2398  READ(cvarmul,fmt=2006) varmul(ig_number_field(jf))
2399  ENDIF
2400  ENDIF
2401  ENDIF
2402 
2403  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'FILLING') THEN
2404  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2405 ! * Get data file name (used to complete the initial field array)
2406  cfilfic(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
2407  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2408 ! * Get logical unit connected to previous file
2409  READ(clvari, fmt=2005) nlufil(ig_number_field(jf))
2410  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 3, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2411 ! * Get filling method
2412  cfilmet(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
2413 ! * If current field is SST
2414  IF (cfilmet(ig_number_field(jf))(4:6) .EQ. 'SST') THEN
2415  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 4, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2416 ! * Get flag for coast mismatch correction
2417  READ(clvari, fmt=2005) nfcoast
2418  IF (cfilmet(ig_number_field(jf))(1:3) .EQ. 'SMO') THEN
2419  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 5, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2420 ! * Get field name for flux corrective term
2421  cfldcor = clvari
2422  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 6, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2423 ! * Get logical unit used to write flux corrective term
2424  READ(clvari, fmt=2005) nlucor
2425  ENDIF
2426  ENDIF
2427  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'CONSERV') THEN
2428  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2429 ! * Get conservation method
2430  cconmet(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
2431  lsurf(ig_number_field(jf)) = .true.
2432  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2433  cconopt(ig_number_field(jf)) = 'bfb'
2434  IF (ilen > 0) THEN
2435  IF (trim(clvari) == 'bfb' .or. trim(clvari) == 'opt' .or. &
2436  trim(clvari) == 'lsum8' .or. trim(clvari) == 'lsum16' .or. &
2437  trim(clvari) == 'gather' .or. trim(clvari) == 'ddpdd' .or. &
2438  trim(clvari) == 'reprosum') THEN
2439  cconopt(ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
2440  ELSE
2441  CALL prtout('ERROR in namcouple conserv argument',jf,1)
2442  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) 'ERROR in namcouple conserv argument '//trim(clvari)
2443  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
2444  ENDIF
2445  ENDIF
2446  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BLASOLD')THEN
2447 ! * Get linear combination parameters for initial fields
2448  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2449 ! * Get main field multiplicative coefficient
2450  READ(clvari, fmt=2012) cafldcobo
2451  ! and convert it accordingly
2452  IF ( index(cafldcobo,'.') == 0 ) then
2453  READ(cafldcobo,fmt=2013) iafldcobo
2454  afldcobo(ig_number_field(jf)) = REAL(iafldcobo)
2455  ELSE
2456  READ(cafldcobo,fmt=2006) afldcobo(ig_number_field(jf))
2457  ENDIF
2458  DO jc = 1, nbofld(ig_number_field(jf))
2459  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
2460  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty)
2461  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2462 ! * Get symbolic names for additional fields
2463  cbofld(jc,ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
2464  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2465 ! * Get multiplicative coefficients for additional fields
2466  READ(clvari, fmt=2012) cabocoef
2467  IF ( index(cabocoef,'.') == 0 ) THEN
2468  READ(cabocoef,fmt=2013) iabocoef
2469  abocoef(jc,ig_number_field(jf)) = REAL(iabocoef)
2470  ELSE
2471  READ(cabocoef,fmt=2006) abocoef(jc,ig_number_field(jf))
2472  ENDIF
2473  ENDDO ! DO jc
2474  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BLASNEW')THEN
2475 ! * Get linear combination parameters for final fields
2476  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2477 ! * Get main field multiplicative coefficient
2478  READ(clvari, fmt=2012) cafldcobn
2479  ! and convert it accordingly
2480  IF ( index(cafldcobn,'.') == 0 ) then
2481  READ(cafldcobn,fmt=2013) iafldcobn
2482  afldcobn(ig_number_field(jf)) = REAL(iafldcobn)
2483  ELSE
2484  READ(cafldcobn,fmt=2006) afldcobn(ig_number_field(jf))
2485  ENDIF
2486  DO jc = 1, nbnfld(ig_number_field(jf))
2487  READ(nulin, fmt=rform) clline
2488  CALL skip(clline, jpeighty)
2489  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2490 ! * Get symbolic names for additional fields
2491  cbnfld(jc,ig_number_field(jf)) = clvari
2492  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 2, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
2493 ! * Get multiplicative coefficients for additional fields
2494  READ(clvari, fmt=2012) cabncoef
2495  IF ( index(cabncoef,'.') == 0 ) THEN
2496  READ(cabncoef,fmt=2013) iabncoef
2497  abncoef(jc,ig_number_field(jf)) = REAL(iabncoef)
2498  ELSE
2499  READ(cabncoef,fmt=2006) abncoef(jc,ig_number_field(jf))
2500  ENDIF
2501  ENDDO ! DO jc
2502  ELSE
2503  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) ' Type of analysis not implemented yet '
2504  WRITE(tmpstr2,*) ' The analysis required in OASIS is :'
2505  WRITE(tmpstr3,*) ' canal = ', canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf))
2506  WRITE(tmpstr4,*) ' with ja = ', ja, ' jf = ', jf
2507  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1,tmpstr2,tmpstr3,tmpstr4)
2508  ENDIF
2509  ENDDO ! DO ja
2510 ! MODIF LC
2511  ENDIF
2512  ENDIF
2513 
2514 !* End of loop on NoF
2515 
2516  ENDDO ! DO jf
2517 
2518 !* Minimum coupling period
2519 
2520  ig_total_frqmin = minval(ig_freq)
2521

2524 2001 FORMAT(a9)
2525 2003 FORMAT(i4)

2528 2006 FORMAT(e15.6)
2529 2008 FORMAT(a2,i4)
2530 2009 FORMAT(a8)
2531 2010 FORMAT(a3,a1,i2)
2532 2011 FORMAT(a3,a1,i8)
2533 2012 FORMAT(a15)
2534 2013 FORMAT(i10)

2536 !* 3. Printing
2537 ! --------
2538  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
2539  IF (nlogprt .GE. 0) THEN
2540  DO jf = 1, ig_final_nfield
2541  IF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_exported ) THEN
2542  cl_print_state = 'EXPORTED'
2543  ELSEIF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_ignored ) THEN
2544  cl_print_state = 'IGNORED'
2545  ELSEIF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_ignout ) THEN
2546  cl_print_state = 'IGNOUT'
2547  ELSEIF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_expout ) THEN
2548  cl_print_state = 'EXPOUT'
2549  ELSEIF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_input ) THEN
2550  cl_print_state = 'INPUT'
2551  ELSEIF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_output ) THEN
2552  cl_print_state = 'OUTPUT'
2553  ELSEIF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_auxilary ) THEN
2554  cl_print_state = 'AUXILARY'
2555  ENDIF
2556 
2557  IF (ig_local_trans(jf) .eq. ip_instant) THEN
2558  cl_print_trans = 'INSTANT'
2559  ELSEIF (ig_local_trans(jf) .eq. ip_average) THEN
2560  cl_print_trans = 'AVERAGE'
2561  ELSEIF (ig_local_trans(jf) .eq. ip_accumul) THEN
2562  cl_print_trans = 'ACCUMUL'
2563  ELSEIF (ig_local_trans(jf) .eq. ip_min) THEN
2564  cl_print_trans = 'T_MIN'
2565  ELSEIF (ig_local_trans(jf) .eq. ip_max) THEN
2566  cl_print_trans = 'T_MAX'
2567  ENDIF
2568 
2569 !* Local indexes
2570  IF (.NOT. lg_state(jf)) THEN
2571  ilab = ig_numlab(jf)
2572  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3001) jf
2573  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3002)
2574  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3003)
2575  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3004)
2576  IF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_input .or. &
2577  ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_output) THEN
2578  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3121) &
2579  cg_input_field(jf), cg_output_field(jf), &
2580  ig_freq(jf), cl_print_trans, &
2581  cl_print_state, ig_total_ntrans(jf)
2582  ELSE
2583  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3116) &
2584  cg_input_field(jf), cg_output_field(jf), &
2585  ig_freq(jf), cl_print_trans, ig_total_nseqn(jf), &
2586  ig_lag(jf), cl_print_state, ig_total_ntrans(jf)
2587  ENDIF
2588  ELSE
2589  ilab = numlab(ig_number_field(jf))
2590  ifcb = len_trim(cficbf(ig_number_field(jf)))
2591  ifca = len_trim(cficaf(ig_number_field(jf)))
2592  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3001) jf
2593  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3002)
2594  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3003)
2595  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3004)
2596  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3005) &
2597  trim(cnaminp(ig_number_field(jf))), &
2598  trim(cnamout(ig_number_field(jf))), &
2599  nfexch(ig_number_field(jf)), &
2600  nseqn(ig_number_field(jf)), &
2601  ig_lag(jf), &
2602  cl_print_state, &
2603  ig_ntrans(ig_number_field(jf))
2604  ENDIF
2605 
2606  IF (.not. lg_state(jf)) THEN
2607  IF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_ignored .or. &
2608  ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_ignout ) THEN

2610  ELSEIF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_input) THEN
2611  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3118) cg_input_file(jf)
2612  ENDIF
2613  ELSE
2614  IF (ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_exported .or. &
2615  ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_expout .or. &
2616  ig_total_state(jf) .eq. ip_auxilary ) &
2617  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3117) cg_restart_file(jf)
2618 
2619  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3007) &
2620  csper(ig_number_field(jf)), nosper(ig_number_field(jf)), &
2621  ctper(ig_number_field(jf)), notper(ig_number_field(jf))
2622  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3008) &
2623  cficbf(ig_number_field(jf))(1:ifcb)//cglonsuf, &

2626  cficbf(ig_number_field(jf))(1:ifcb)//csursuf, &
2627  cficaf(ig_number_field(jf))(1:ifca)//cglonsuf, &
2628  cficaf(ig_number_field(jf))(1:ifca)//cglatsuf, &
2629  cficaf(ig_number_field(jf))(1:ifca)//cmsksuf, &
2630  cficaf(ig_number_field(jf))(1:ifca)//csursuf
2631  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3009)
2632  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3010)
2633  DO ja = 1, ig_ntrans(ig_number_field(jf))
2634  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3011) ja, canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf))
2635  IF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'MAPPING') THEN
2636  write(nulprt1, fmt=3048) &
2637  trim(cmap_file(ig_number_field(jf))), &
2638  trim(cmaptyp(ig_number_field(jf))), &
2639  trim(cmapopt(ig_number_field(jf)))
2640  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'SCRIPR') THEN
2641  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3045) &
2642  cmap_method(ig_number_field(jf)), &
2643  cfldtype(ig_number_field(jf)), &
2644  cnorm_opt(ig_number_field(jf)), &
2645  crsttype(ig_number_field(jf)), &

2649  ENDIF
2650  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'CONSERV') THEN
2651  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3025) &
2652  cconmet(ig_number_field(jf)), &
2653  cconopt(ig_number_field(jf))
2654  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BLASOLD') THEN
2655  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3027) &
2656  trim(cnaminp(ig_number_field(jf))), &
2657  afldcobo(ig_number_field(jf))

2661  cbofld(jc,ig_number_field(jf)), &
2662  abocoef(jc,ig_number_field(jf))

2664  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'BLASNEW') THEN
2665  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3027) &
2666  trim(cnamout(ig_number_field(jf))), &
2667  afldcobn(ig_number_field(jf))
2668  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3028) nbnfld(ig_number_field(jf))
2669  DO jc = 1, nbnfld(ig_number_field(jf))
2670  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3030) &
2671  cbnfld(jc,ig_number_field(jf)), &
2672  abncoef(jc,ig_number_field(jf))
2673  ENDDO
2674  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'CHECKIN') THEN

2676  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'CHECKOUT') THEN
2677  WRITE(nulprt1,*) ' '
2678  ELSEIF (canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf)) .EQ. 'LOCTRANS') THEN
2679  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt=3047) cl_print_trans
2680  ELSE
2681  WRITE(tmpstr1,*) ' Type of analysis not implemented yet '
2682  WRITE(tmpstr2,*) ' The analysis required in OASIS is :'
2683  WRITE(tmpstr3,*) ' canal = ',canal(ja,ig_number_field(jf))
2684  WRITE(tmpstr4,*) ' with ja = ', ja, ' jf = ', jf
2685  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1,tmpstr2,tmpstr3,tmpstr4)
2686  ENDIF
2687  ENDDO ! DO ja
2688  ENDIF
2689  ENDDO ! DO jf
2690  ENDIF
2691  ENDIF
2692 
2693 !* 4. End of routine
2694 ! --------------
2695 
2696  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
2697  IF (nlogprt .GE. 0) THEN
2698  WRITE(nulprt1,*)' '
2699  WRITE(nulprt1,*) subname,'-- End of ROUTINE --'
2700  CALL oasis_flush (nulprt1)
2701  ENDIF
2702  ENDIF

3246 
3247 !****
3248 ! *****************************
3249 ! * OASIS ROUTINE - LEVEL 1 *
3250 ! * ------------- ------- *
3251 ! *****************************
3252 !
3253 !**** *prtout* - Print output
3254 !
3255 ! Purpose:
3256 ! -------
3257 ! Print out CHARACTER string and one INTEGER value
3258 !
3259 !** Interface:
3260 ! ---------
3261 ! *CALL* *prtout(cdtext, kvalue, kstyle)*
3262 !
3263 ! Input:
3264 ! -----
3265 ! cdtext : CHARACTER string to be printed
3266 ! kvalue : INTEGER variable to be printed
3267 ! kstyle : printing style
3268 !
3269 ! Output:
3270 ! ------
3271 ! None
3272 !
3273 ! Workspace:
3274 ! ---------
3275 !
3276 ! Externals:
3277 ! ---------
3278 ! None
3279 !
3280 ! Reference:
3281 ! ---------
3282 ! See OASIS manual (1995)
3283 !
3284 ! History:
3285 ! -------
3286 ! Version Programmer Date Description
3287 ! ------- ---------- ---- -----------
3288 ! 2.0 L. Terray 95/10/01 created
3289 ! 2.3 L. Terray 99/02/24 modified: X format for NEC
3290 !
3291 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
3292 
3293  IMPLICIT NONE
3294 !
3295 !* ---------------------------- Include files ---------------------------
3296 !
3297 !
3298 !* ---------------------------- Argument declarations ----------------------
3299 !
3300  CHARACTER(len=*),intent(in) :: cdtext !< character string to be printed
3301  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p),intent(in) :: kvalue !< integer to be printed
3302  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p),intent(in) :: kstyle !< printing style
3303 
3304 !* ---------------------------- Local declarations ----------------------
3305 
3306  INTEGER(kind=ip_intwp_p) :: ilen,jl
3307  CHARACTER*69 cline
3308  CHARACTER(len=*),PARAMETER :: cbase = '-'
3309  CHARACTER(len=*),PARAMETER :: cprpt = '* ===>>> :'
3310  CHARACTER(len=*),PARAMETER :: cdots = ' ------ '
3311  CHARACTER(len=*),parameter :: subname='(mod_oasis_namcouple:prtout)'
3312 
3313 !* ---------------------------- Poema verses ----------------------------
3314 
3315 ! CALL oasis_debug_enter(subname)
3316 
3317 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
3318 
3319 !* 1. Print CHARACTER string + INTEGER value
3320 ! --------------------------------------
3321 
3322  IF (mpi_rank_global == 0) THEN
3323  IF ( kstyle .EQ. 1 .OR. kstyle .EQ. 2) THEN
3324  cline = ' '
3325  ilen = len(cdtext)
3326  DO jl = 1, ilen
3327  cline(jl:jl) = cbase
3328  ENDDO
3329 
3330  IF ( kstyle .EQ. 2 ) THEN
3331  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt='(/,A,1X,A)') cdots, cline
3332  ENDIF
3333  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt='(A,1X,A,1X,I18)') cprpt, cdtext, kvalue

3336  WRITE(nulprt1, fmt='(/,A,1X,A,1X,I18,/)') cprpt, cdtext, kvalue

3351 !> Searches for a particular keyword in the namcouple file
3352 
3353 SUBROUTINE findkeyword (keyword, line, found)
3354 
3355 !****
3356 ! *****************************
3357 ! * OASIS ROUTINE - LEVEL T *
3358 ! * ------------- ------- *
3359 ! *****************************
3360 !
3361 !**** *findkeyword* - Searches for a particular keyword in the namcouple file
3362 !
3363 ! Purpose:
3364 ! -------
3365 ! Find the line with the specified keyword
3366 !
3367 !** Interface:
3368 ! ---------
3369 ! *CALL* *findkeyword (keyword, line, found) *
3370 !
3371 ! Input:
3372 ! -----
3373 ! keyword : string to search for (CHARACTER string)
3374 !
3375 ! Output:
3376 ! ------
3377 ! line : full line that contains the keyword (CHARACTER string)
3378 ! found : flag indicating whether keyword was found (logical)
3379 !
3380 ! History:
3381 ! -------
3382 ! Version Programmer Date Description
3383 ! ------- ---------- ---- -----------
3384 ! 3.3 T. Craig 2016/08/02 created
3385 !
3386 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
3387 !
3388  IMPLICIT NONE
3389 !
3390 !* ---------------------------- Include files ---------------------------
3391 !
3392 !
3393 !* ---------------------------- Argument declarations -------------------
3394 !
3395  CHARACTER (len=*) , INTENT ( in) :: keyword !< keyword string
3396  CHARACTER (len=*) , INTENT (out) :: line !< line containing keyword
3397  LOGICAL , INTENT (out) :: found !< flag if keyword was found
3398 !
3399 !* ---------------------------- Local declarations -------------------
3400 !
3401  CHARACTER (len=jpeighty) :: clline
3402  CHARACTER (len=jpeighty) :: clvari
3403  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p):: ILEN, ios, ios2
3404  CHARACTER(len=*),parameter :: subname='(mod_oasis_namcouple:findkeyword)'
3405 !
3406 !* ---------------------------- Poema verses ----------------------------
3407 
3408 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
3409 
3410 ! CALL oasis_debug_enter(subname)
3411 
3412  found = .false.
3413  ios2 = 0
3414 
3415  rewind nulin
3416  DO WHILE (.not.found)
3417  READ(nulin, fmt=rform, end=110, iostat=ios2) clline
3418  if (ios2 == 0) then
3419  CALL skip(clline,jpeighty, ios=ios)
3420 ! write(nulprt1,*) trim(subname),'tcx1: ',trim(clline)
3421  IF (ios == 0) THEN
3422  CALL parse(clline, clvari, 1, jpeighty, ilen, __line__)
3423 ! write(nulprt1,*) trim(subname),'tcx2: ',trim(clvari),trim(keyword)
3424  IF (clvari == adjustl(keyword)) THEN
3425  line = clline
3426  found = .true.
3427  ENDIF
3428  ENDIF
3429  else
3430  goto 110
3431  endif
3432  ENDDO
3433 
3434 110 CONTINUE
3435 
3436 ! CALL oasis_debug_exit(subname)
3437  return
3438 
3439 END SUBROUTINE findkeyword

3514 !> Subroutine to parse string
3515 
3516 SUBROUTINE parse (cdone, cdtwo, knumb, klen, kleng, line)
3517 
3518 !****
3519 ! *****************************
3520 ! * OASIS ROUTINE - LEVEL T *
3521 ! * ------------- ------- *
3522 ! *****************************
3523 !
3524 !**** *parse* - Parsing routine
3525 !
3526 ! Purpose:
3527 ! -------
3528 ! Find the knumb'th string in cdone and put it in cdtwo.
3529 ! A string is defined as a continuous set of non-blanks CHARACTERs
3530 !
3531 !** Interface:
3532 ! ---------
3533 ! *CALL* *parse (cdone, cdtwo, knumb, klen, kleng)*
3534 !
3535 ! Input:
3536 ! -----
3537 ! cdone : line to be parsed (char string)
3538 ! knumb : rank within the line of the extracted string (INTEGER)
3539 ! klen : length of the input line (INTEGER)
3540 ! line : line where parse is called (INTEGER)
3541 !
3542 ! Output:
3543 ! ------
3544 ! cdtwo : extracted CHARACTER string (char string)
3545 ! kleng : length of the extracted string (INTEGER)
3546 !
3547 ! Workspace:
3548 ! ---------
3549 ! None
3550 !
3551 ! Externals:
3552 ! ---------
3553 !
3554 ! Reference:
3555 ! ---------
3556 ! See OASIS manual (1995)
3557 !
3558 ! History:
3559 ! -------
3560 ! Version Programmer Date Description
3561 ! ------- ---------- ---- -----------
3562 ! 2.0 L. Terray 95/09/01 created
3563 ! O. Marti 2000/11/08 simplify by using F90
3564 ! CHARACTER functions
3565 ! 3.3 T. Craig 2016/08/02 updated
3566 !
3567 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
3568 !
3569  IMPLICIT NONE
3570 !
3571 !* ---------------------------- Include files ---------------------------
3572 !
3573 !
3574 !* ---------------------------- Argument declarations -------------------
3575 !
3576  CHARACTER (len=*) , INTENT (inout) :: cdone !< line to parse
3577  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p), INTENT ( in) :: knumb !< rank within line of extracted string
3578  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p), INTENT ( in) :: klen !< length of input line
3579  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p), INTENT ( in) :: line !< file line number of call
3580  CHARACTER (len=*) , INTENT (out) :: cdtwo !< extracted string
3581  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p), INTENT (out) :: kleng !< length of extracted string
3582 !
3583 !* ---------------------------- Local declarations -------------------
3584 !
3585  INTEGER(kind=ip_intwp_p) :: ii,jl
3586  CHARACTER (len=klen) :: clline
3587  CHARACTER (len=klen) :: clwork
3588  CHARACTER (len=1), SAVE :: clblank = ' ', clcmt = '#'
3589  CHARACTER(len=*),parameter :: subname='(mod_oasis_namcouple:parse)'
3590 !
3591 !* ---------------------------- Poema verses ----------------------------
3592 
3593 ! CALL oasis_debug_enter(subname)
3594 !
3595 ! %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
3596 
3597 !* - Abort if line is a comment
3598 
3599  IF (checkcomment(cdone)) THEN
3600  write(tmpstr1,*) subname,' ERROR comment line found:', trim(cdone)
3601  write(tmpstr1,*) subname,' ERROR called from :',line
3602  CALL namcouple_abort(subname,__line__,tmpstr1)
3603  ENDIF
3604 
3605 !* - DO the extraction job
3606 !* - Fill temporary string and remove leading blanks
3607 
3608  clwork = adjustl(cdone)
3609 
3610 !* - Fill cdtwo with blanks
3611 
3612  cdtwo = clblank
3613 
3614 !* - If there are no more CHARACTERs, kleng=-1
3615 
3616  IF ( len_trim( clwork) .LE. 0) THEN
3617  kleng = -1
3618 ! CALL oasis_debug_exit(subname)
3619  RETURN
3620  ENDIF
3621 
3622 !* - If this is the one we're looking for, skip
3623 ! otherwise go knumb-1 more sets of CHARACTERs
3624 
3625  IF (knumb .GE. 2) THEN
3626  DO jl = 1, knumb-1
3627  ii = index( clwork, clblank) - 1
3628  clwork( 1:ii) = clblank
3629  clwork = adjustl( clwork)
3630 
3631 !* - If there are no more CHARACTERs, kleng=-1
3632 
3633  IF (len_trim( clwork) .LE. 0) THEN
3634  kleng = -1
3635 ! CALL oasis_debug_exit(subname)
3636  RETURN
3637  ENDIF
3638  ENDDO
3639  ENDIF
3640 
3641 !* - Find the length of this set of CHARACTERs
3642 
3643  kleng = index( clwork, clblank) - 1
3644 
3645 !* - Copy to cdtwo
3646 
3647  cdtwo( 1:kleng) = clwork( 1: kleng)
3648 
3649 ! CALL oasis_debug_exit(subname)
3650 
3651  return
3652 
3653 END SUBROUTINE parse

3659 SUBROUTINE skip (cd_one, id_len, endflag, ios)
3660 
3661 !**** SKIP
3662 !
3663 ! Purpose:
3664 ! Find next non-comment line
3665 !
3666 ! Interface:
3667 ! CALL skip (cd_one, id_len, endflag)
3668 !
3669 ! Method:
3670 ! Read the first CHARACTER of the line and skip line if
3671 ! it is a comment
3672 !
3673 ! External:
3674 ! none
3675 !
3676 ! Files:
3677 ! none
3678 !
3679 ! References:
3680 !
3681 ! History:
3682 ! --------
3683 ! Version Programmer Date Description
3684 ! ------------------------------------------------
3685 ! 2.5 A.Caubel 2002/04/04 created
3686 ! 3.3 T. Craig 2016/08/02 updated
3687 !
3688 !*-----------------------------------------------------------------------
3689 !
3690  IMPLICIT NONE
3691 !
3692 !** + DECLARATIONS
3693 !
3694 !
3695 !** ++ Include files
3696 !
3697 !** ++ Argument declarations
3698 !
3699  CHARACTER(len=*),intent(inout) :: cd_one !< namcouple line
3700  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p),intent(in) :: id_len !< length of line
3701  LOGICAL, optional, intent(inout) :: endflag !< flag indicating eof reached
3702  INTEGER (kind=ip_intwp_p), OPTIONAL, INTENT(out) :: ios !< return code
3703 !
3704 !** ++ Local declarations
3705 !
3706  CHARACTER(len=id_len) :: cl_line
3707  LOGICAL :: found
3708  CHARACTER(len=*),parameter :: subname='(mod_oasis_namcouple:skip)'
3709 !
3710 !*-----------------------------------------------------------------------
3711 !
3712 ! CALL oasis_debug_enter(subname)
3713 
3714  IF (present(endflag)) endflag = .false.
3715  IF (present(ios)) ios = 0
3716  cl_line = cd_one
3717  found = .false.
3718 
3719  DO WHILE (.not.found)
3720  IF (checkcomment(cl_line)) THEN
3721  READ(nulin, fmt=rform, end=140, iostat=ios) cl_line
3722  ELSE
3723  found = .true.
3724  ENDIF
3725  ENDDO
3726 
3727 140 CONTINUE
3728 
3729  IF (found) THEN
3730  cd_one = cl_line
3731  ELSE
3732  IF (present(endflag)) endflag = .true.
3733  IF (PRESENT(ios)) ios = -1
3734  ENDIF
3735 
3736 ! CALL oasis_debug_exit(subname)
3737  RETURN
3738 
3739 END SUBROUTINE skip
